# Understood. Focusing strictly on notifications that are not related to direct messages. Here are some sensible notifications for your platform that add value to the student and teacher experience.

# ## For Students üéì

#     Purchase Confirmation

#         When: Immediately after a student successfully buys a lesson.

#         Title: Purchase Successful!

#         Description: "Your purchase of '[Lesson Title]' is complete. You can access it now in your personal library."

#         Why it makes sense: This is a critical transactional receipt. It gives the student confidence in their purchase and a clear next step.

#     New Lesson From a Teacher

#         When: A teacher the student has purchased from before publishes a new lesson.

#         Title: New Lesson from [Teacher's Name]

#         Description: "[Teacher's Name] just published a new lesson you might like: '[Lesson Title]'."

#         Why it makes sense: This drives repeat business by alerting interested students to new, relevant content from teachers they already trust.

#     Rating Reminder

#         When: A few days after a student has purchased a lesson.

#         Title: How was '[Lesson Title]'?

#         Description: "Share your feedback by rating the lesson. Your review helps other students and supports the teacher."

#         Why it makes sense: This helps build a strong community feedback system, which increases the quality and trustworthiness of your platform.

# ## For Teachers üë®‚Äçüè´

#     Lesson Sale Confirmation üí∞

#         When: A student buys one of the teacher's lessons.

#         Title: You've Made a Sale!

#         Description: "Congratulations! Your lesson '[Lesson Title]' was just purchased by a student."

#         Why it makes sense: This is a powerful and motivating notification for teachers, providing immediate positive reinforcement and a real-time update on their sales.

#     New Lesson Rating Received ‚≠ê

#         When: A student submits a rating for one of the teacher's lessons.

#         Title: New Rating for '[Lesson Title]'

#         Description: "You've received a new [4/5] star rating for your lesson from a student."

#         Why it makes sense: This provides teachers with crucial feedback on their content and helps them track their reputation on the platform.

#     Lesson Approved and Published

#         When: (If you have an admin review process) An admin approves the teacher's submitted lesson.

#         Title: Your Lesson is Live!

#         Description: "Your lesson, '[Lesson Title]', has been approved and is now available in the marketplace."

#         Why it makes sense: This is an important status update that closes the loop on the content creation process for the teacher.

#     Weekly Performance Summary

#         When: Sent automatically once a week.

#         Title: Your Weekly Performance Summary

#         Description: "This week you earned [$Amount], sold [X] lessons, and received [Y] new ratings. View your dashboard for more details."

#         Why it makes sense: This acts as a mini-report that keeps teachers engaged and informed about their business performance without requiring them to constantly check their dashboard.